missionEventData.data2: In the far reaches of the Outer Rim a rebellion is forming. A rebel cell led by the frigate Redemption and ace pilot Keyan Farlander have been striking back against the evil galactic empire. But the Emperor is at the height of his power, and even now he is marshalling his forces at the edge of the mid-rim. But help has come from the most unlikely of places. The captain of an imperial corvette has sent the rebel freedom fighters a secret message, he wishes to defect...

missionEventData.data1: With the aid of our Sullustan allies we have secured docking codes for the Invincible! With this information in hand we have formed a plan for putting an end to Imperial aggression in this sector. Using a stolen Imperial Shuttle we are going to place a bomb in the Invincible's hangar bay. To do this we need a vessel outfitted to current Imperial specifications. Alliance intelligence has identified such a target at an Imperial Testing site run by the Cygnus Corporation. Red Squadron will provide cover while Gold Squadron jumps in to disable the shuttle, before the Dagger jumps in to complete the boarding. Good luck.
Red Squadron head to the jump point immediately.
Looks like they're testing a new model of fighter. Their identification beacon is reading X-G1 Star Wing.
Those Star Wings are heading straight for us. Red Squadron break formation and engage.
This is Gold Leader. The shuttle has been disabled. Activating beacon for boarding craft.
This is Dagger One. The target is marked and we're moving to engage.
It took a little persuading, but the Cygnus staff have kindly relinquished control of the shuttle. Moving to jump point.
There are still fighters active. Clear them out so we can safely make the jump to Hyperspace.
Okay Red Squadron. Head to the jump point.
Looks like that Ton Folk has teeth. Detecting four Tie Fighters launching.
Another group of Tie Fighters are launching!
Looks like they've had enough. The Ton Folk is preparing to jump.
See you back at the rendezvous Red One.
ANA - M12 Recover The Ars Opus
missionEventData.data3: With the docking codes and shuttle secured everything is in place for the final act. Our technical staff has been working around the clock to create a proton explosion strong enough to fracture the Invincible from the inside. This could be the end of Imperial authority in this sector, pray that nothing goes wrong
